    <p>10 March 2023</p>
    <h2 id="email-settings-10032023" class="govuk-heading-m">Changes to email settings</h2>
    <p>We have made some changes to the ways we collect and use your email addresses in form settings.</p>
    <p>Firstly, we have removed the 'from' address setting. This is because it was causing some emails to end up in spam folders. But we still want your form emails to look and behave as if they are coming from your service, not from the MoJ Forms team. To help with this, we have made 2 other changes:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>added your form name to the 'from' field in all emails</li>
    <li>added a reply address to the confirmation email template</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Now, when your form sends an email - either the submission email to you or the confirmation email to your users - it will show as coming from your form name.</p>
    <p>In addition, the confirmation email template now includes a field for a reply address. This is an address that emails will go to if a user chooses to reply to the email. You need to include this even if you don't want users to reply. Users may reply anyway and could include personal information. For data protection purposes, these emails should only go to your team.</p>
    <p>Overall, these changes should make setting up your form emails a little simpler and more intuitive.</p>
    <p>Learn more about <a class="govuk-link" href="/settings/#confirmation-email">sending users a confirmation email</a> in the user guide.</p>
    <p><a class="govuk-link" href="#top">Back to top</a></p>
